The paper deals with the problem of inferring haplotypes from mate-pair reads, which involves algorithms and data structures for efficient processing of large amounts of genomic data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a generative model and connections with decoding convolutional codes, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with genomic data, which is a topic of interest in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
